<br>
My pet ripped up the mob with a couple nukes from me while the rest of the group got the other mob to about 40%.  When the group saw &quot;you gain experience&quot; from my mob they were in complete shock that my pet with help from me were able to do the damage we did.<br>
<br>
This is nothing new in the mage community, but why don't other people realize the utility and power of the mage? <p>Khalendor Dayze</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2410<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 11:05:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7880.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages...a dying class?</span><hr size=1> All pet groups.<br>
