<br>
Another method I like is palling up with necro/mage/wizards and killing stuff.  Two epic mages can kill mobs in PoV by chain casting and light nuking.  Mana is not an issue if you use manage your mana, use focus earring, rods, and petcanni (4% mana per pet reclaim).  A lot us tend to be as bias as the people we are complaining about.  Unwilling to be creative and mix it up in the event an ideal group doesnt come our way.  Take 3 mages LFG group and head to PoJ basement but if you are sitting on arse for 13hrs its cause your sitting waiting for someone to hand you a group.  Therefore its your own fault.<br>
<br>
I agree with the soloing aspect.  I find completely unfair that classes such as wizzies, druids, necros, shamen can solo effectively.  You can attribute this to being the only pure casting class without a crowd control spell.   For all your links about wizzies getting screwed in the expansion or the druid I have seen both classes med quading for 20% aa experience per round.  Of our guild advancing Druids and Wizzys were amoung the first to hit 65.  Saying those classes got shafted is mute to me.  They stand tall in empowerment compared to other classes in the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rabidsheep>rabidsheep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/02 4:57:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7880.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages...a dying class?</span><hr size=1> I soloed the last 1.5 yellow bub to lvl 65 in PoV today.<br>
