<br>
When I solo in pov, I do it with air pet. I get a sow, and hopefully a hp buff. Then I pull a larvae with malosini, and try to land a blast before sending pet.<br>
Pet is buffed with velocity and BO5 and has taunt off.<br>
I aggro kite it, that is posseble because the 61 air pet is stunning rather good<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  eventually my pet will get aggro and die, I will just chain pets... Very easy to chain now that the pets enrage. Blast it down, doing like 15k dmg per mob in blasts, cann back my mana in between.<br>
<br>
This got a LOT easier when I got suspend minion 2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Then I would have a pet that is fully buffed, if I can steal some shammy buffs that was also nice, because this pet didnt get aggro.. it was sent on mob after the hp's had dropped to ca 40%.<br>
<br>
I have soloed a named larvae this way, and the undeads by the hut. I havent tried desert yet, but I think its fully doable<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I did test making the second pet a water pet, for the exstra dmg, but that didnt work... he is running SLOW! even with velocity he couldnt catch the mob.<br>
<br>
63 fire was also tested, for the stuns. but he dont work, he is also rooting<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and when the mob is rooted, SPLAT!<br>
<br>
This is a lot of work, and you would need some AA's to make it efficient (elemental pact, SCM, suspended minon are the most important. SCF helps). The exp is about the same as in gruop (sometimes better, sometimes worse) so its only something I do while only on a couple of minutes or when LFG.<br>
<br>
Rabids 65 mage<br>
